div.p: A message broker that as many services as possible register to and notify the indexer.
Federation of message brokers should be possible. I.e. having one message broker per discipline.

How hard is it to implement RabbitMQ support into the dummy identifier service and the pit-service? As I currently do not move the data out of their old repositories, base-repo can not notify the Indexer for existing data (in other places).

div.p: The way Elastic works should fit pretty good to queries for records. Indexes are similar to JSON Schemes, which are similar to the Kernel Information Profiles. It should be possible to map records and type specific queries into elasticsearch, since the key of an attribute is a unique PID, implicitly representing a type.
